A beeswarm plot or swarmplot is a type of data visualization that displays individual data points in a way that they don’t overlap, resulting in a swarming effect that resembles a swarm of bees.

Basic beeswarm plot

library(ggbeeswarm)
library(ggplot2)

# Data generation
set.seed(1234)
data <- data.frame(
  value = rnorm(2000),
  group = sample(c("G1", "G2", "G3"), size = 2000, replace = TRUE)
)

head(data)
##        value group
## 1 -1.2070657    G3
## 2  0.2774292    G1
## 3  1.0844412    G3
## 4 -2.3456977    G3
## 5  0.4291247    G1
## 6  0.5060559    G3

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, colour=group)) +
  geom_beeswarm()

Customizing color and theme

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, colour=group)) +
  geom_beeswarm() +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07"))

Changing dots size

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, colour=group)) +
  geom_beeswarm(size=0.5) +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07"))

Changing dots position

Available options for dots position:

  • swarm: the default method
  • compactswarm: similar to swarm, but the points are more compact
  • center: the points are centered on the x-axis
  • hex: the points are positioned in hexagons
  • square: the points are positioned in squares

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, colour=group)) +
  geom_beeswarm(size = 0.5, method = "swarm") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07"))

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, colour=group)) +
  geom_beeswarm(size = 0.5, method = "compactswarm") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07"))

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, colour=group)) +
  geom_beeswarm(size = 0.5, method = "center") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07"))

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, colour=group)) +
  geom_beeswarm(size = 0.5, method = "hex") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07"))

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, colour=group)) +
  geom_beeswarm(size = 0.5, method = "square") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07"))

Splitting the plot

With side=1L it will be on the right side of the axis and with side=-1L it will be on the left side of the axis.

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, 
                 colour=group)) +
  geom_beeswarm(size=0.5,side = -1L) +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07")
  )

ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, 
                 colour=group)) +
  geom_beeswarm(size=0.5,side = 1L) +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07")
  )
